# Windows Event Viewer Investigation

## Goal

Learn how Windows records authentication events and how analysts investigate them.

## Skills Practiced

- Windows Event Viewer
- Event IDs
- Authentication Logs
- Log Correlation
- Basic Investigation

## What I Learned

- Difference between Event IDs 5379 and 5382
- How SYSTEM accounts differ from user accounts
- Why I wasn't seeing Event ID 4688
- How to verify Windows audit policies

## Project Files

- 2-Event Viewer.pdf

## Reflection
I was pleased to see that a lot of questions I had were answered upon clicking into each ID. 
Information such as what an ID meant, who requested it, when etc. I also think that an enterprise 
environment will have considerably more, so I am grateful for that information.

## More to Explore
- Explore all 13 Windows logon types.
- Enable Process Creation auditing.
- Learn more about OpenSSH logs.
- Investigate Event ID 4688 once auditing is enabled.
